Introduction:
The Employee Resignation Survey System is a software application designed to analyze the reasons behind employee resignations within a company. This system collects and processes data related to employee resignations, enabling organizations to identify patterns, address concerns, and improve retention strategies. The insights gained help businesses create better work environments and reduce attrition rates.

Objectives:
To collect feedback from employees who are resigning.
To identify common reasons for employee turnover.
To analyze trends in resignation data.
To provide actionable insights to improve employee retention.
To streamline exit interviews and surveys.
